Grafana Alert Routing to Internal Alert System
Dummy runbook for the Airflow CPU Utilization alert

1. Purpose
Grafana alerts need to be sent to an internal alert system. The internal alert system receives events through a Lambda function created by the DaaS/internal alert system developer. Grafana must send alerts in a JSON format that the Lambda can parse and transform into the internal alert object.
This document focuses only on the Airflow CPU Utilization alert first. After this alert works end-to-end, the same pattern can be reused for other Grafana alerts.
2. Current Dummy Architecture
Grafana Alert Rule
  -> Contact Point: EXAMPLE-PRD-Alerts-SNS-INTERNAL
  -> SNS Topic: arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:111122223333:EXAMPLE-PRD-Alerts
  -> SQS Queue: arn:aws:sqs:us-east-1:111122223333:example-prd-alerts-queue
  -> Lambda: example-alert-transformer-lambda
  -> Internal Alert System API
  -> Internal Alert UI
Note: The Grafana query, threshold, and labels can remain mostly unchanged. The key change is the message body that Grafana sends to SNS.
3. Why the Change Is Needed
The Lambda expects a JSON string. If Grafana sends the default/plain text alert message, Lambda parsing can fail when it tries to run json.loads(message).
Grafana should send a structured JSON payload with alerts, status, labels, and annotations.
{
  "alerts": [
    {
      "status": "firing",
      "labels": {
        "alertname": "...",
        "component": "...",
        "account_id": "...",
        "resource": "...",
        "region": "...",
        "stage": "...",
        "subsys": "..."
      },
      "annotations": {
        "description": "..."
      }
    }
  ]
}
4. Exact Place to Replace in Grafana
Replace the template in the Grafana Contact Point, not in the alert rule query or threshold section.
Grafana
  -> Alerting
  -> Contact points
  -> EXAMPLE-PRD-Alerts-SNS-INTERNAL
  -> Edit
  -> AWS SNS integration
  -> Message / Message body / Notification message field
  -> Replace the existing default Grafana template with the custom JSON template
  -> Save contact point
Do not replace these alert rule fields for this change:
Summary
Description
Runbook URL
Labels
Query
Threshold
Those fields can stay as-is initially. The important field is the SNS contact point message body.
