6. Custom JSON Template to Paste in the Contact Point
Paste the following template into the Contact Point message field. It uses only dummy infrastructure values.
{
  "alerts": [
    {{- range $i, $alert := .Alerts }}
    {{- if $i }},{{ end }}
    {
      "status": {{ printf "%q" $alert.Status }},
      "labels": {
        "alertname": "Airflow High CPU Utilization",
        "component": "EXAMPLE_APP",
        "account_id": "111122223333",
        "resource": "Airflow CPU Utilization",
        "region": "us-east-1",
        "stage": "prd",
        "subsys": "aws/example-mwaa"
      },
      "annotations": {
        "description": "Airflow CPU Utilization is above threshold 80% in prd us-east-1."
      }
    }
    {{- end }}
  ]
}
Note: This template makes the SNS message body valid JSON so the Lambda can parse it.
